Entity Details
User
Represents a registered user of the application.

id: Unique identifier for the user.
username: Display name for the user.
email: Contact email (unique).
password: Hashed password string.
avatar: URL to the user's profile picture.
Anime
Represents an anime title in the database.

id: Unique identifier (likely from initial data source like AniList).
title: Main display title.
cover: URL to the cover image.
banner: URL to the banner image.
format: Media format (e.g., TV, Movie).
episodes: Total number of episodes.
status: Airing status (e.g., Finished, Airing).
season: Release season (e.g., Fall, Winter).
year: Release year.
genres: List of associated genres.
description: Synopsis of the anime.
Favorite (Relationship)
Note: Currently, the frontend implementation uses localStorage to store favorites locally on the client's device. However, strictly following the 
db.json
 structure implies a backend storage for favorites to sync across devices.

In a database context, this entity resolves the Many-to-Many relationship between Users and Anime.

user_id: Foreign key referencing a User.
anime_id: Foreign key referencing an Anime.
